Sarah is involved in the analysis of research on topics as varied as speech and language impairment, sexual assault, instructional technology, and family dynamics while collaborating with faculty and graduate students. She also teaches quantitative methodology courses for graduate students.

# Education

-   PhD in Statistics, 2017

-   MS in Statistics, 2006

-   BS Math & Chem Teaching, 2000

    Utah State University
